---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = (import.meta.env.BASE_URL || "/").replace(/\/?$/, "/");
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How It Works | Any Debt Collections — Simple 4-Step Recovery Process"
  description="Discover how Any Debt Collections recovers your money in 4 clear steps. Free consultation, account handover, active recovery, monthly payments — no upfront fees."
>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!--  HERO                                     -->
  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="hiw-hero">
    <div class="container hiw-hero-inner">
      <span class="eyebrow reveal">The Process</span>
      <h1 class="hiw-hero-heading reveal delay-1">
        From First Call to<br />Cash in Your Account
      </h1>
      <p class="hiw-hero-sub reveal delay-2">
        Our recovery process is designed to be simple for you and relentless for your debtors. Four clear steps, full transparency at every stage, and no cost unless we collect.
      </p>
      <div class="hiw-steps-preview reveal delay-3">
        <a href="#step-1" class="hiw-step-pill">
          <span class="hiw-step-pill-num">01</span>
          Free Consultation
        </a>
        <span class="hiw-step-arrow" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"/></svg>
        </span>
        <a href="#step-2" class="hiw-step-pill">
          <span class="hiw-step-pill-num">02</span>
          Handover Your Accounts
        </a>
        <span class="hiw-step-arrow" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"/></svg>
        </span>
        <a href="#step-3" class="hiw-step-pill">
          <span class="hiw-step-pill-num">03</span>
          Recovery in Action
        </a>
        <span class="hiw-step-arrow" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"/></svg>
        </span>
        <a href="#step-4" class="hiw-step-pill">
          <span class="hiw-step-pill-num">04</span>
          You Get Paid
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!--  STEP 1: FREE CONSULTATION                -->
  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section id="step-1" class="step-section light">
    <div class="container step-inner">
      <div class="step-content reveal-left">
        <div class="step-badge">
          <span class="step-badge-num">01</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="step-heading">Free Consultation</h2>
        <p class="step-lead">
          Every engagement begins with a conversation — no paperwork, no commitment, no cost.
        </p>
        <p class="step-body">
          You reach out to us via phone, WhatsApp, or email. We'll arrange a time to talk through your situation — how many accounts you have outstanding, what type of debtors you're dealing with (individuals, businesses, schools, patients), the amounts involved, and how long the accounts have been overdue.
        </p>
        <p class="step-body">
          This initial consultation has one purpose: to understand your needs so we can tell you clearly whether we can help and what our approach would be. There is no obligation to proceed. There is no consultation fee. And there is no sales pitch — just an honest conversation about your debt situation and what a professional recovery effort would look like.
        </p>
        <p class="step-body">
          By the end of the call, you'll know exactly how we work, what our commission structure is, and what you can realistically expect in terms of recovery outcomes. You'll also have the opportunity to ask anything — about our process, our experience, or our compliance practices.
        </p>

        <div class="step-detail-box">
          <h3 class="step-detail-title">What to expect in your consultation:</h3>
          <ul class="step-detail-list">
            <li class="step-detail-item">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              A review of your outstanding account portfolio
            </li>
            <li class="step-detail-item">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              Honest assessment of recovery prospects
            </li>
            <li class="step-detail-item">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              Explanation of our full service offering
            </li>
            <li class="step-detail-item">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              Commission rate and payment structure explained clearly
            </li>
            <li class="step-detail-item">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              Your questions answered — no pressure to commit
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step-aside reveal-right delay-2">
        <div class="step-visual-card">
          <div class="step-visual-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="36" height="36" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M22 16.92v3a2 2 0 0 1-2.18 2 19.79 19.79 0 0 1-8.63-3.07A19.5 19.5 0 0 1 4.69 12a19.79 19.79 0 0 1-3.07-8.67A2 2 0 0 1 3.56 1.27h3a2 2 0 0 1 2 1.72c.127.96.361 1.903.7 2.81a2 2 0 0 1-.45 2.11L7.91 8.81a16 16 0 0 0 6 6l.86-.86a2 2 0 0 1 2.11-.45c.907.339 1.85.573 2.81.7a2 2 0 0 1 1.72 2.03z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="step-visual-title">Book Your Free Call</h3>
          <p class="step-visual-body">Speak directly with Angelique. No scripts, no call centre — just a real conversation about your accounts.</p>
          <div class="step-contact-options">
            <a href="tel:+27621165638" class="step-contact-option">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M22 16.92v3a2 2 0 0 1-2.18 2 19.79 19.79 0 0 1-8.63-3.07A19.5 19.5 0 0 1 4.69 12a19.79 19.79 0 0 1-3.07-8.67A2 2 0 0 1 3.56 1.27h3a2 2 0 0 1 2 1.72c.127.96.361 1.903.7 2.81a2 2 0 0 1-.45 2.11L7.91 8.81a16 16 0 0 0 6 6l.86-.86a2 2 0 0 1 2.11-.45c.907.339 1.85.573 2.81.7a2 2 0 0 1 1.72 2.03z"/></svg>
              062 116 5638
            </a>
            <a href="mailto:anycollections@outlook.com" class="step-contact-option">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 4h16c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2v12c0 1.1-.9 2-2 2H4c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V6c0-1.1.9-2 2-2z"/><polyline points="22,6 12,13 2,6"/></svg>
              Email Us
            </a>
            <a href={`${base}contact`} class="btn btn-primary btn-full">Book Online</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step-reassurance">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
          <span>No obligation. No pressure. No cost.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!--  STEP 2: HANDOVER YOUR ACCOUNTS           -->
  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section id="step-2" class="step-section dark">
    <div class="container step-inner reverse">
      <div class="step-aside reveal-left delay-2">
        <div class="step-visual-card dark-card">
          <div class="step-visual-icon dark-vicon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="36" height="36" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/><polyline points="10 9 9 9 8 9"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="step-visual-title dark-vtitle">What You'll Need</h3>
          <ul class="step-info-list">
            <li class="step-info-item">
              <span class="step-info-dot"></span>
              Debtor names and ID / registration numbers
            </li>
            <li class="step-info-item">
              <span class="step-info-dot"></span>
              Contact details (last known phone, email, address)
            </li>
            <li class="step-info-item">
              <span class="step-info-dot"></span>
              Outstanding balance per account
            </li>
            <li class="step-info-item">
              <span class="step-info-dot"></span>
              Original invoice, statement, or account record
            </li>
            <li class="step-info-item">
              <span class="step-info-dot"></span>
              Date of last payment (if any)
            </li>
            <li class="step-info-item">
              <span class="step-info-dot"></span>
              Any previous communication with the debtor
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="step-info-note">Don't have all of this? Don't worry — we'll tell you what's essential and work with what you have.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step-content reveal-right">
        <div class="step-badge dark-badge">
          <span class="step-badge-num">02</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="step-heading dark-heading">Handover Your Accounts</h2>
        <p class="step-lead dark-lead">
          Once you're ready to proceed, the handover process is straightforward and handled entirely by us.
        </p>
        <p class="step-body dark-body">
          We'll send you a simple service agreement that sets out our terms — the commission rate, what services are included, how reporting works, and how payments are made. This agreement is plain language and transparent. Once signed, you are protected and so are we.
        </p>
        <p class="step-body dark-body">
          You then provide us with your account list. This is typically a spreadsheet or your existing debtor records — whatever format you work in. We need the key information about each debtor: their name, contact details, the outstanding balance, and the documentation supporting the debt (an invoice, statement, or signed agreement). We'll let you know exactly what's needed and guide you through any gaps.
        </p>
        <p class="step-body dark-body">
          From the moment accounts are handed over, you hand over the burden. You don't need to make calls, send letters, or deal with difficult conversations. That's our job. You get on with running your business while we get on with recovering your money.
        </p>

        <div class="step-detail-box dark-detail-box">
          <h3 class="step-detail-title dark-detail-title">Your role after handover:</h3>
          <ul class="step-detail-list">
            <li class="step-detail-item dark-detail-item">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              Receive and review monthly reports
            </li>
            <li class="step-detail-item dark-detail-item">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              Inform us if a debtor contacts you directly
            </li>
            <li class="step-detail-item dark-detail-item">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              Add new accounts as they arise
            </li>
            <li class="step-detail-item dark-detail-item">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              Everything else — we handle it
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!--  STEP 3: RECOVERY IN ACTION               -->
  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section id="step-3" class="step-section light">
    <div class="container step-inner">
      <div class="step-content reveal-left">
        <div class="step-badge">
          <span class="step-badge-num">03</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="step-heading">Recovery in Action</h2>
        <p class="step-lead">
          This is where the work happens. Systematic, persistent, and fully documented.
        </p>
        <p class="step-body">
          Once accounts are loaded, we begin the recovery programme immediately. Each debtor receives a formal initial contact — a written demand that clearly states the outstanding amount, the basis of the debt, and a deadline for payment or engagement. This is professional and measured, designed to prompt action without damaging your relationship with the debtor any further than necessary.
        </p>
        <p class="step-body">
          If there's no response, we follow up. Phone calls, SMS, email — we use every legitimate channel of communication on a structured schedule. If a debtor engages and requests a payment arrangement, we assess the proposal and come back to you with their offer. If a debtor continues to ignore contact, we escalate: formal demand letters, and where appropriate, credit bureau listings.
        </p>
        <p class="step-body">
          For debtors who have disappeared or changed their contact details, our tracing service runs concurrently. When a debtor is located, the recovery programme picks up immediately. No delays, no restart — the process continues from where it left off.
        </p>

        <div class="step-recovery-grid">
          <div class="step-recovery-card reveal delay-1">
            <div class="step-rec-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M4 4h16c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2v12c0 1.1-.9 2-2 2H4c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V6c0-1.1.9-2 2-2z"/><polyline points="22,6 12,13 2,6"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h4 class="step-rec-title">Written Demands</h4>
            <p class="step-rec-body">Formal letters establishing the debt and demanding payment within a defined period.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="step-recovery-card reveal delay-2">
            <div class="step-rec-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M22 16.92v3a2 2 0 0 1-2.18 2 19.79 19.79 0 0 1-8.63-3.07A19.5 19.5 0 0 1 4.69 12a19.79 19.79 0 0 1-3.07-8.67A2 2 0 0 1 3.56 1.27h3a2 2 0 0 1 2 1.72c.127.96.361 1.903.7 2.81a2 2 0 0 1-.45 2.11L7.91 8.81a16 16 0 0 0 6 6l.86-.86a2 2 0 0 1 2.11-.45c.907.339 1.85.573 2.81.7a2 2 0 0 1 1.72 2.03z"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h4 class="step-rec-title">Phone Follow-Ups</h4>
            <p class="step-rec-body">Scheduled calls at defined intervals — professionally conducted, every response documented.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="step-recovery-card reveal delay-3">
            <div class="step-rec-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="11" cy="11" r="8"/><line x1="21" y1="21" x2="16.65" y2="16.65"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h4 class="step-rec-title">Tracing</h4>
            <p class="step-rec-body">Nationwide skip-tracing for debtors who have relocated or changed their contact details.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="step-recovery-card reveal delay-4">
            <div class="step-rec-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h4 class="step-rec-title">Bureau Listings</h4>
            <p class="step-rec-body">Credit bureau listings for persistent non-payers — a powerful legal tool to prompt settlement.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step-aside reveal-right delay-2">
        <div class="step-visual-card">
          <div class="step-visual-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="36" height="36" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="22 12 18 12 15 21 9 3 6 12 2 12"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="step-visual-title">The Recovery Escalation Path</h3>
          <div class="escalation-path">
            <div class="escalation-step">
              <span class="esc-dot esc-dot-1"></span>
              <div class="esc-content">
                <strong>Initial Demand</strong>
                <span>Formal written contact with payment deadline</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="escalation-step">
              <span class="esc-dot esc-dot-2"></span>
              <div class="esc-content">
                <strong>Scheduled Follow-Ups</strong>
                <span>Phone, SMS, email at structured intervals</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="escalation-step">
              <span class="esc-dot esc-dot-3"></span>
              <div class="esc-content">
                <strong>Tracing (if needed)</strong>
                <span>Locate the debtor if contact details are outdated</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="escalation-step">
              <span class="esc-dot esc-dot-4"></span>
              <div class="esc-content">
                <strong>Bureau Listing</strong>
                <span>Formal listing for persistent non-payers</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!--  STEP 4: YOU GET PAID                     -->
  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section id="step-4" class="step-section dark">
    <div class="container step-inner reverse">
      <div class="step-aside reveal-left delay-2">
        <div class="step-visual-card dark-card">
          <div class="step-visual-icon dark-vicon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="36" height="36" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="1" y="4" width="22" height="16" rx="2" ry="2"/><line x1="1" y1="10" x2="23" y2="10"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="step-visual-title dark-vtitle">Monthly Payment Flow</h3>
          <div class="payment-flow">
            <div class="pay-step">
              <span class="pay-arrow" aria-hidden="true">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
              </span>
              <div class="pay-step-text">
                <strong>We collect from debtors</strong>
                <span>During the month, as payments come in</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="pay-step">
              <span class="pay-arrow" aria-hidden="true">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
              </span>
              <div class="pay-step-text">
                <strong>Month-end reconciliation</strong>
                <span>Total collected is tallied and commission deducted</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="pay-step">
              <span class="pay-arrow" aria-hidden="true">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
              </span>
              <div class="pay-step-text">
                <strong>Report delivered</strong>
                <span>Monthly report sent with full account status</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="pay-step pay-final">
              <span class="pay-arrow pay-final-arrow" aria-hidden="true">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
              </span>
              <div class="pay-step-text">
                <strong>EFT to your account</strong>
                <span>Balance transferred directly to you</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step-content reveal-right">
        <div class="step-badge dark-badge">
          <span class="step-badge-num">04</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="step-heading dark-heading">You Get Paid</h2>
        <p class="step-lead dark-lead">
          Every rand collected on your behalf comes back to you — reliably, monthly, and with full documentation.
        </p>
        <p class="step-body dark-body">
          When debtors pay, the money is received and held in our accounts. At the close of each month, we reconcile all collections across your account portfolio. Our commission is calculated and deducted at this point — you never need to invoice us or track what's owed. The balance is then transferred directly to your bank account by EFT.
        </p>
        <p class="step-body dark-body">
          Together with your payment, you receive your monthly report. This details every account we worked during the month, what actions were taken, and which accounts generated the collections reflected in your payment. There's a clear, auditable connection between the report and the transfer — nothing is vague, nothing is unexplained.
        </p>
        <p class="step-body dark-body">
          This monthly cycle continues for as long as you have accounts with us. New accounts can be added at any time. Settled accounts are closed and removed from the active portfolio. You stay in full control of what we're working and what gets closed.
        </p>

        <div class="step-detail-box dark-detail-box">
          <h3 class="step-detail-title dark-detail-title">What makes our payment model clean:</h3>
          <ul class="step-detail-list">
            <li class="step-detail-item dark-detail-item">
